  // 5 beta 005
  - PDF Generation;
  - Many Bug Fixes;


  // 5 betta 004 (2003-10-20)
  - Tool for mege database results into a document (Merge tool) was finnaly ported to this last version;
  - Tool for generate address labels (label tool) was finnaly ported to this last version;
  - New features in Merge Tool (tab stops, margin setup);
  - Preview of report in a tree format (according to report levels definition);
  - improvements and fixed bugs in report preview;
  - fixed bugs in number format;
  - fixed bugs reggarding column sizes;
  
  // 5 betta 003 2003-08-13 (1.7 Mb)
  - AgataAPI (You can run your reports from any PHP application);
  - New tool for Diagrams generation, new layout;
  - New tool for graph generation (by lines and by columns), new layout;
  - Faster Connection times (improvements on loading DB structure);
  - Import DBF and CSV formats is working again;
  - Save as (new button);

  // 5 beta 002 2003-07-09 (1.9 Mb)
  - Created Report Repository (report browser);
  - Total interface redesign;
  - Automatic Group by;
  - Internal classes reconstructed;
  - Export as XML (with sub-totals and grand-total);
  - Master/Detail interface redesigned;
  - auto-link among tables (just register the table links);
  - Export as Diagrams
    Now Agata draws the lines linking the tables.
  - Created Table Families
    Tables are grouped in Families;
  - Created DataDescription interface
    You can set friend names to tables and fields (masks).
  - Running fine with Oracle on Windows;

  // 5 beta 001 2003-04-07 (1.2 Mb)
  - Export as HTML;
  - Better Configuration Tool
    (Configure HTML colors and fonts, aplication directories...);
  - Total Parameters support (EIS too);
  - Export as CSV (Main Screen);
  - Many enhancements (Confirmation Dialogs, Message boxes);
  - Improvements in export as PS (with Groups);


